HEADWORD: chlortetracycline
<hw>chlortetracycline</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a yellow crystalline
antibacterial antibiotic used to treat certain bacterial and rickettsial
diseases. <altname>Aureomycin</altname> is one common trademark for
chlortetracycline.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Aureomycin.</syn>⟦br⟧
